<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-07-01T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-07-01T13:00:00-05:00" n="95" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d95">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">838.00Electoral Law/7: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Chargé in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gross</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-07-01T14:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">July 1,
                                        1927—2 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>38. Department wishes you to telegraph present status of the electoral
                            law and whether there is any possibility of enactment of the proposed
                            law in near future, in which event you will request delay until the
                            Department is able to express its views. The Department has not approved
                            any final draft of such a law.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Olds</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>